.SH NAME
.PP
dropCS \- Delete a specified collection space.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]db.dropCS(<name>,[options])\f[]\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Sdb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Delete a specified collection space.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]name\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[]， \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Collection space name.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]options\f[] ( \f[I]Object\f[]， \f[I]Optional\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
The options for dropping the collection space, could be a combination of the
following options:
.IP "1." 3
\f[C]EnsureEmpty\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[] ): Ensure the collection space is empty or
not, default to be false.
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
true: when collection space contains collection, dropping is canceled and return
with error code \-275 ; when collection space does not contain any collection,
dropping is proceed.
.IP \[bu] 2
false: dropping is proceed whether collection space contains collection or not.
.PP
Format: \f[C]EnsureEmpty:true|false\f[]
.RE
.RE
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, the specified collection space is dropped.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
